    "state_reason": "completed",
    "title": "Bitcoin binaries are not signed",
    "body": "For Windows builds, only the setup executable is signed. On Windows, it's customary for publishers to sign both the setup and binaries. I understand signing the executable doesn't increase tamper resistance during download. However, signing the run-time executable provides the following advantages:\n- any UAC dialog box will show Bitcoin Foundation as the publisher\n- it allows users who don't use the setup executable to verify the program's authenticity\n- the executable can later be verified for any tampering (especially when running across USB drives)\n",
